Here is a simple JavaScript code that takes in a user's age and returns the current year plus their age:
```
// Get the current year
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();

// Get the user's age from the input field
const age = parseInt(prompt("Enter your age:"));

// Calculate the future year
const futureYear = currentYear + age;

// Display the result
alert(`In ${age} years, you will be ${futureYear} years old.`);
```
